<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="567" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2625</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of
                                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-11">November 11,
                                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>The Italian Ambassador called this afternoon and left with me the
                                    accompanying communication<note n="5" xml:id="d567fn5">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                                    </note> which has just been presented by the Italian Government
                                    to all the states members of the League. The Ambassador was also
                                    instructed to communicate it to this Government and in doing so
                                    expressed the opinion that the same communication was being made
                                    to all governments non-members of the League. Signor Rosso
                                    translated the communication into French and read it to me. He
                                    said that he regarded it as an exceedingly important and very
                                    serious communication.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>